article.headline: Lipscomb 69, North Florida 54
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Jordan Burgason scored a team-high 15 points to lead Lipscomb to a 67-54 win against North Florida in the Atlantic-Sun Conference opener for both teams on Thursday night. Adnan Hodzic notched a double-double with 14 points and 11 rebounds, as did Michael Teller with 10 points and 10 boards. The Bisons (3-3, 1-0) shot 50 percent from the field (21 of 42) en route to victory, and outrebounded the Ospreys 44-22. Corez Riley scored a game-high 20 points for the Ospreys (0-6, 0-1), who shot 34.7 percent (17 of 49) in the loss. The Ospreys closed the gap in the second half after trailing 35-19 at the half, but a 4-for-21 night from beyond the 3-point arc helped sink North Florida.
